devdoc.author: Ali Murtaza Memon
devdoc.details: This contract uses the ERC721URIStorage extension of ERC721 which provides the way to update the token uri with function `_setTokenURI`.

NFTMinted(address,uint256,uint256).details: This event will be emitted inside mintNft function.

params.owner: will be address who call the mintNft function.
params.tokenId: will be the token id which user will have minted.
params.value: will be the amount on which NFT will be minted.

Withdraw(uint256,uint256).details: This event will be emitted inside withdraw function.

params.amount: will be the amount owner will withdraw at the timestamp.
params.timestamp: will be the time of withdrawl.

params.mintFee: will be the fee required to mint an NFT.
params.name: will be the name of the token.
params.nftTokenUri: will be the token metadata ipfs hash.
params.symbol: will be the symbol of the token.

mintNft().details: here I am using the _setTokenURI function to set the token uri.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

devdoc.title: NFT - A ERC721URIStorage version of smart contract.

mintNft().notice: mintNft will mint the NFT on the blockchain.

withdraw().notice: withdraw will transfer all of the sold nfts funds to owner of the contract.

userdoc.notice: This contract will mint ERC721 (aka NFT - Non-Fungible-Token) token
